title: Grateful Dead Live at Jai-Alai Fronton on 1974-06-23
description:
Set 1

Ramble On Rose, Black Throated Wind, Mississippi Half Step, Beat It On Down The Line, Row Jimmy, Jack Straw, Let It Rock, Cumberland Blues, El Paso, To Lay Me Down, Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Weather Report Suite Part 1-> Let It Grow-> China Doll

Set 2

Phil & Ned-> Ship of Fools, Big River, Black Peter, Around & Around, Dark Star-> Spanish Jam-> U.S. Blues, Uncle John's Band-> One More Saturday Night, E: Casey Jones

reviews.review_text:
great sound, great show Who doesn't love June 1974?  Here's a famous show with a nice 24 bit matrix mix.  (AUDs from this era sound fantastic.)  I even like the first set -- lots of sideways, counterintuitive solo moves from Garcia.  
Good work, Wally; thank you, seeders.
https://thoughtsonthedead.wordpress.com/2015/07/25/miami-wall-of-sound-machine/

Cumberland The tease of Sugarfoot Rag towards the end of Cumberland Blues had me wondering what the heck that noodle was that I had never heard before.   Yesterday, I heard Sugarfoot Rag on the radio and it immediately clicked. When stuff is sneaked in like this, it makes the Dead the Dead for me. Very cool.

Sugarfoot Rag I didnt know the name of that lick for a long time but found a reference to it on a message board here.

I know it also appears in the 5/25/72 Dark Star and the Cumberland on 10/2/72.  Anyone know of others?
